{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"carefree-gushy-argusfish","description":"## Why\n\nThe enriched sidecars (stories A–C) and the existing attestations are reachable today only via\nscattered internal helpers, and there is no single call that returns a ticket's FULL retained review\nhistory or resolves its associated code reviews. The follow-on audit UI epic and any script need one\ndocumented read surface.\n\n## What\n\nA read layer that, for a ticket id, returns: (a) the full retained history (not just latest) of\nplan-review sidecars; (b) the completion attestation plus any completion sidecar record; (c) the\nassociated code reviews, resolved via the ticket's inbound `relates_to` links from `code_review`\ntickets, each with its full sidecar history. Exposed as a library function, a CLI command, and a\nread-only MCP tool.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py` and `src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py` — add\n  `all_review_results(ticket)` history enumerators (walk the ticket's `REVIEW_RESULT` events\n  newest→oldest, schema-tolerant), complementing the existing `latest_*` readers.\n- New `src/rebar/audit/read.py` — an `audit_trail(ticket_id)` aggregator composing the plan /\n  completion / code-review histories, resolving code reviews via the ticket's `relates_to` links\n  (reusing `rebar.show` / `rebar.list_tickets`), returning a typed dict.\n- CLI `rebar audit show <ticket> [--output json]`; a read-only MCP tool `audit_trail`.\n\n## Approach rationale\n\nA single aggregator over the existing readers + the existing `relates_to` links reuses the linkage\nthe reviewbot already writes (`emit_code_review_artifact` links each code-review artifact\n`relates_to` its work ticket), so no new linking mechanism is introduced — the read layer only\ntraverses links that already exist. The MCP tool is read-only so it is available regardless of\n`REBAR_MCP_READONLY`.\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\nPure addition (new readers + new command + new read-only tool); no existing behavior changes.\nSchema-tolerant readers accept both v1 and v2 records. Reverting removes the new surface with no\ndata impact.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `audit_trail(ticket_id)` returns the full retained plan-review history, the completion record,\n      and the code reviews linked via `relates_to`, newest-first. Oracle: an integration test seeding\n      a ticket with multiple plan-review sidecars, a completion record, and a `relates_to`-linked\n      `code_review` ticket with its own sidecar, then asserting the aggregate contains all of them in\n      order.\n- [ ] `rebar audit show <ticket> --output json` prints the same structure. Oracle: a CLI subprocess\n      test (test-design §3 CLI) asserting on the emitted JSON.\n- [ ] The MCP `audit_trail` tool returns the structure and is read-only (available even with\n      `REBAR_MCP_READONLY=1`). Oracle: a test invoking the tool handler under that env.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"46f0-4e09-b8ed-4a4e","parent_id":"ba33-2310-f6c6-4bd6","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"audit read layer (full-history readers + relates_to resolution + CLI/MCP)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784067243332948001,"uuid":"ce7580b6-3fb8-4976-bb18-8cda0740cc89"}